WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Hexit' is a Workbench game which displays two hexagonal shaped
boards filled with coloured tiles. One of these boards has a
pattern and the other is randomly shuffled. The goal is to move
the tiles of the shuffled board in order to match the other board,
in the least amount of moves possible.

  You play by clicking on a tile, which must be surrounded by 6
other tiles. Each time you click on a tile, the game will 'rotate'
the surrounding tiles clockwise by one position.

 Have fun!

